data.title: Biography
data.meta_description: Rob Ford. Writer: Rob Ford's Words in the Mouth of a Child. Rob Ford was born on 28 May 1969 in Etobicoke, Ontario, Canada. He was an actor and writer, known for Rob Ford's Words in the Mouth of a Child (2014), Toronah (2015) and WingMen (2016). He was married to Renata Brejniak. He died on 22 March 2016 in Toronto, Ontario, Canada.
data.text:
Father Douglas Bruce Ford (Sr.) represented the riding of Etobicoke-Humber in the Ontario provincial legislature from 1995 to 1999, for the Progressive-Conservative party. He was a "backbencher", meaning a Member of the Legislative Assembly (MLA) that did not hold a position in Premier Mike Harris' cabinet.

[to members of Toronto City Council, after being stripped of most of his mayoral powers] This, folks, reminds me of when, and I was watching with my brother, when Saddam attacked Kuwait, and President Bush said, "I warn you. I warn you. I warn you. Do not." Well, folks, if you think American style politics is nasty, you guys have just attacked Kuwait.
